Ford GoBike System Analysis¶

Onyeukwu Stephen¶

Introduction¶

The system provides users with a convenient and affordable mode of transportation in urban areas, including San Francisco and the Bay Area. Users can rent bicycles at designated stations and return them at any other station within the network. The Ford GoBike system data includes information on the number of bikes rented, trip duration, start and end stations, and other factors that can help analyze and improve the system's performance and user experience.

Define¶

Extract different dateparts from start_time to form new date columns

Code¶

In [27]:
#Creating a function to create new columns that extracts part of a previous date column
def process_date_column(bike_df_copy, date_column_name):
    # Define a dictionary of column names and their respective format strings
    format_strings = {
        "start_date": "%Y-%m-%d",
        "start_hour_of_day": "%H",
        "start_day_of_week": "%A",
        "start_month": "%B"
    }
    # Iterate over the dictionary items
    for column_name, format_string in format_strings.items():
         # Create a new column in the dataframe with the formatted date information
        bike_df_copy[column_name] = bike_df_copy[date_column_name].dt.strftime(format_string)
    # Return the processed dataframe
    return bike_df_copy

fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=3, figsize=(20,5))
week_order = ['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday']

sns.countplot(data=bike_df_copy, x='start_day_of_week', hue='member_gender', ax=ax[0], order=week_order)
ax[0].set_xlabel('Day of Week');
ax[0].set_ylabel('Count');
ax[0].set_title("Weekly usage between Gender", fontsize=10)
ax[0].set_xticklabels(week_order,rotation=90)

sns.countplot(data=bike_df_copy, x='start_day_of_week', hue='user_type', ax=ax[1],order=week_order)
ax[1].set_xlabel('Day of the week');
ax[1].set_ylabel('Count');
ax[1].set_title("Weekly usage between customers and subscribers",fontsize=10)
ax[1].set_xticklabels(week_order,rotation=90)

sns.countplot(data=bike_df_copy, x='user_type', hue='bike_share_for_all_trip', ax=ax[2])
ax[2].set_xlabel('User_type');
ax[2].set_ylabel('Count');
ax[2].set_title("User_type usage for bike share",fontsize=10)

plt.show()

Observation¶

  • Male gender used the bike renting more from monday to sunday, followed by the female and other gender group in that order.
  • There were much more subscribers than coustomers overall. The difference between subscribers' and constomers weekend usage reveals that subscribers use bikes mostly for getting to and from work during the week, while customers weekend usage shows that subscribers use bikes primarily for leisure, touring, and relaxing.
  • The customers do not have a package that allows for bike sharing, even though the subscriber could share they had way more less bike sharing compared to the shared ones.

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 5))
sns.pointplot(data=bike_df_copy, x='start_day_of_week', y='duration_sec', hue='user_type', dodge=0.1, linestyles="", ax=ax,order = week_order)

ax.set_xlabel('Day of the week', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
ax.set_ylabel('Avg. Trip Duration in Seconds', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
ax.set_title('Average Trip Duration Vary in weekdays between User Type', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')

ax.legend(title='User Type', fontsize=12)
ax.grid(color='gray', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.5)

plt.show()

Observation¶

According to the graph above, subscribers travel more quickly than regular customers every day of the week. Trip time notably increases on Saturdays and Sundays for both user categories, particularly for customer. The average duration of subscriber usage was significantly more consistent than that of all customers from Monday through Friday.

Conclusions¶

  • The highest number of trips were taken in the on thursdays and Tuesday, weekends (Saturday and Sunday) had the lowest number of trips.
  • A higher percentage of the users are subscribers accounting for about 91%, while the customer take up 9%.
  • The male gender were more represented among the users in Ford Go-bike.
  • The number of trips peak from 7am-9am during daytime and 4pm -7pm in the evening
  • Customer spend longer time on trips compared to subscribers
  • Male gender spend slightly shorter tine on trips compared to Female/Other gender
  • No subscription package available for customers to share trips
  • Customer travel longer duration regardless of the day of the week than the subscribers.
  • For both types of users the other gender group spent more time on trips, this is then followed by the female then male in that order
